After nearly a 20-day voyage, Swiss Bertrand Piccard and British Brian Jones completed their nonstop circumnavigation on a hot-air balloon and landed in southern Egypt smoothly morning.
Achieving what promoters called the last great milestone of aviation, Piccard and Jones joined legends like the Wright Brothers and Charles Lindbergh with 's completion of the first manned round-the-world balloon flight.
The first two, Piccard of Switzerland and Jones of Britain, completed a 20-day trip together, ending in the Egyptian desert.
The International Olympic Committee said that they will award the Olympic Order to balloonists Piccard and Jones who are the first.
